OL,3,CWatchdog finds insufficient police
OL,4,Ctraining before 9-year-old boy's murder
OL,6,FThe watchdog looked at 20 interactions
OL,7,Fbetween West Mercia Police and Alfie,
OL,8,Fhis mother and her partner between
OL,9,FMarch 2018 and February 2021, but
OL,10,Ffound that there was "no indication of
OL,11,Fmisconduct" by any individual officer.
OL,13,FThere had been a "significant amount
OL,14,Fof contact" with the force in the
OL,15,Fyears before the child died, but the
OL,16,Ffamily home had a "climate of fear"
OL,17,Fwhich meant Alfie was allegedly asleep
OL,18,Fduring the occasions the police were
OL,19,Fcalled to the property, the watchdog
OL,20,Fsaid.
OL,26,@rD@VOUsD@KO]uD@ROUvD@KO]xD@SOUxD@cO]
