OL,3,CWatchdog finds insufficient police
OL,4,Ctraining before 9-year-old boy's murder
OL,6,FOn one occasion, six months before
OL,7,FAlfie was murdered, a neighbour rang
OL,8,Fpolice because they could hear a man
OL,9,Fshouting and someone "thrashing around
OL,10,Fin the bath", and said: "Maybe he's
OL,11,Fbeing hit and held under the water".
OL,13,FTwo officers checked on Alfie, who
OL,14,Fappeared to be asleep in his room,
OL,15,Fafter this incident.
OL,17,FThey did not have police powers to
OL,18,Fremove Howell from the home despite
OL,19,Fconcerns, so they contacted children's
OL,20,Fservices the next day.
